    rec("RLN-P1-C06-Entry6-2-1", "For any complex numbers $a$, $b$, $\\lambda$, and $q$, with $|q|<1$, define $G(a,b,\\lambda):=G(a,\\lambda;b;q):=\\displaystyle\\sum_{n=0}^{\\infty}\\frac{(-\\lambda/a;q)_n a^n q^{n(n+1)/2}}{(q;q)_n(-bq;q)_n}$. Then $\\displaystyle\\frac{G(aq,b,\\lambda q)}{G(a,b,\\lambda)}=\\cfrac{1}{1+\\cfrac{aq+\\lambda q}{1+\\cfrac{bq+\\lambda q^2}{1+\\cfrac{aq^2+\\lambda q^3}{1+\\cfrac{bq^2+\\lambda q^4}{1+\\cdots}}}}}$. Set $P(a,b,\\lambda)=(-bq;q)_{\\infty}G(a,b,\\lambda)$."),
